</subtitle><entry><title type="html">Tizonia’s new web!</title><link href="https://www.tizonia.com/news/2017/10/02/tizonia-new-web/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Tizonia's new web!" /><published>2017-10-02T23:23:00+01:00</published><updated>2017-10-02T23:23:00+01:00</updated><id>https://www.tizonia.com/news/2017/10/02/tizonia-new-web</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://www.tizonia.com/news/2017/10/02/tizonia-new-web/">&lt;p&gt;The Tizonia Project has from today a new web site!.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.simplybuilt.com/&quot;&gt;SimplyBuilt&lt;/a&gt;, the web builder app and hosting
shop that has been very kindly (and for free) hosting Tizonia’s website in the
last few years is &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.simplybuilt.com/farewell-and-thanks&quot;&gt;closing
down&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it has been necessary to find a new place.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Luckily, finding a replacement has been extremely easy. &lt;a href=&quot;https://pages.github.com/&quot;&gt;GitHub
Pages&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://jekyllrb.com/&quot;&gt;Jekyll&lt;/a&gt; are
these days the ‘de-facto’ standard in free hosting for open source
projects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So here it is, the new site and blog for Tizonia.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The site is based on the really nice
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/aksakalli/jekyll-doc-theme&quot;&gt;jekyll-doc-theme&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-get remove ruby
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-get autoremove
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-add-repository ppa:brightbox/ruby-ng
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-get update
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-get upgrade
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo apt-get install ruby2.4 ruby2.4-dev
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo gem update --system
    &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;$ &lt;/span&gt;sudo gem install jekyll bundler bundle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name>juanrubio</name></author><summary type="html">The Tizonia Project has from today a new web site!.</summary></entry></feed>